content: My now 8 year old loved the game when he was 4 and will still play it but the spelling list is way below his level now. It would be great to have higher level words available.
This is a great free game. My 5&6 year old love it and is definitely helping them their spelling
Cant understand half the words that's are said.
Its to good but because you cant use your own words its sum boring
Horrible. Crashes on the startup screen. Uninstalling
This game doesnt give you the freedom to use whatever word you want to. Unless you like to guess what they want you to guess each round, then go ahead.

This game is great for kids 5-9 my daughter loves it and its such an excellent idea. Only complaints are the audio sounds self recorded in front of a laptop or pc and i wish i could choose a girl or boy. I look forward to future games from you.

My child loves it. The only problem that interferes with her learning is that the main voice actress was recorded with a crappy microphone, and some words she says are ambiguous. Path sounds like hat, teen sounds like team, etc.  Other than that oversight, it is mostly really well conceived and implemented.
